@flexiarg coordination/par-as-obligation
@title PAR as Obligation (G0)
@keywords par, retrospective, obligation, evidence
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/stop-the-line]

! conclusion:
  If you want the library evolution loop to have usable signals, require a PAR (post-action review) before closing a coordinated session and treat its absence as a gate rejection.

  + context: Without PAR, the system accumulates execution without learning.
  + IF:
    you want the system to improve patterns and coordination over time

  + HOWEVER:
    evidence without retrospective interpretation does not produce tensions or canonicalization candidates

  + THEN:
    require a PAR record at G0, minimally capturing what worked, what did not, and suggested improvements

  + BECAUSE:
    PAR is the bridge between Level 0 execution and Level 1 library evolution

